# JSON-RPC Bridge — See packages/sdk

The full protocol rules (envelope shape, origin validation, how to add a new
method/event) live in `packages/sdk/.cursor/rules/json-rpc-protocol.mdc` —
read that file before changing `rpc-bridge.ts` or the handlers passed into
`useRpcBridge` in `App.tsx`.

The one widget-specific rule: RPC method handlers (the object passed to
`useRpcBridge`) should stay thin — delegate the actual work to a hook or
`lib/` function (`fetchProperty`, `applyTheme`, ...) rather than inlining
logic in the handler itself.
